<div class="page-header">
  <h1>Nodefony start in <strong>pre-production </strong>mode</h1>
</div>


<div class="doc2 jumbotron">

<p>
	<strong><h2>MODE  pre-production </h2></strong>

	This mode can be useful if you want to check the proper functioning of the production environment <br>
	<ul>
		<li>  Use Node Clusters </li>
		<li>  Use caches control (views , controller ...) </li>
		<li>  Use Webpack config in production mode (uglyfyjs, uglyfycss ...) </li>
	</ul>
</p>

</div>

<h2>Location :</h2>
<div class="doc2">
	<p>
    In nodefony Root directory launch <code>nodefony preprod</code>
	</p>

	<pre>
    .
    ├── CHANGELOG.md
    ├── LICENSE.txt
    ├── README.md
    ├── app
    ├── bin
    ├── config
    ├── doc
    ├── node_modules
    ├── package-lock.json
    ├── package.json
    ├── src
    ├── tmp
    ├── web
    └── yarn.lock
	</pre>
</div>

